00:01:05.990 --> 00:01:10.120
So now we're going to look at the other end
of the spectrum which is daytime without rain.

00:01:10.120 --> 00:01:13.400
You can see the reflections are a lot sharper
on the car too.

00:01:13.400 --> 00:01:16.580
The main light source now is just the sun.

00:01:16.580 --> 00:01:20.090
Obviously the windshield wipers have stopped
rolling, and the reflection on the car windows

00:01:20.090 --> 00:01:21.340
is a lot smoother.

00:01:21.340 --> 00:01:25.070
You're not being bombarded with light sources
like you are when it is darker outside.

00:01:25.070 --> 00:01:28.410
The clouds seem to move at the same speed,
and the shadows like the one from that nearby

00:01:28.410 --> 00:01:30.450
tree are a lot darker.

00:01:30.450 --> 00:01:35.880
Lastly I just want to look at the sunrise
and sunset in Project CARS at a speed of 240

00:01:35.880 --> 00:01:37.270
